This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) as it discusses the transfer of generalization ability from a large neural network to a smaller one. It also involves the training of a student model to match the probabilities assigned by a teacher model, which is a common technique in machine learning. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of neural networks for classification tasks, which is a common application of machine learning. Other likely sub-categories include artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), computational linguistics (cs.CL), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), as these fields also involve the use of neural networks and classification tasks.
